updates:
Welcome to SHOPsears!
Updated: February 10, 2017
Enhancement:

  • Transfer of Cart: is now enabled for all stores. Simply create your cart in SHOPsears as you do now, then transfer and retrieve at POS with your sales ID. Pairing is a thing of the past! All payment is now handled by the register â including checks! Refer to the Transfer of Cart Job Aid in the SHOPsears User Guide (available in the Menu) and in SHCConnect for further information as well as FAQs.

Reminder:
  • User Guide: Available through the MENU. This provides training documents as well as all pertinent job aids.
  • Close the Sale: This feature is intended to increase close rates by providing new âPersonalized Offersâ. This functionality will provide SYW members with real-time targeted offers which can be used in the event that the associate feels an additional discount may save the sale.
  • Duress Availability: This is part of the new LMS2 that has just been released. Check out the Product Results page for this new feature. When a member is in immediate need of an item you can use their criteria to narrow the results; then use the Product Availability button to determine delivery dates. What a great way to service our members!.
  • Priority Leads Dashboard: The new Leads page shows a Recap Summary with WTD, Rolling 28 Days and YTD tabs. All leads, including Meet with an Expert, are in one place. Closed leads can be searched by member or by a date range. Check out the job aids in the User Guide for more details.
  • Mobile Phone Validation: Mobile phone fields will now validate the number.
    • Tips:

    Associate Log In:

    • Do you ever pick up an iPad or handheld and you are not sure if you are logged in? Your name can be found on the Updates page. Select Updates from the Menu at any time to view this.

      NOTE: The associate logged into SHOPsears must use his/her Associate ID on the register to retrieve their cart.

    Device Management:

  • Make sure your devices and sleds are all fully functioning. Please direct your management team to report broken iPads, iHelds and sleds in a timely manner. They can call the Service Desk at 1-800-998-1500 to create a service request to get a shipping label sent to your store. Don't wait to ship multiple devices at a time; use 2-Day shipping.
    Ensure that all devices are plugged in and charging each night.

  • NOTE: Only the larger brick will properly charge the iPad. These can be ordered through Ariba â item MD836LL/A.
    If you are not able to log into a device when receiving it back from the Depot pebble the serial number in the SHOPsears pebble group so it can be provisioned to your store.

    • Support:

  • Please use the Report an Issue function to report any feedback or issues you have with SHOPsears. Your issues will display in the SHOPsears Pebble group.Support teams are closely monitoring this Pebble group and can assist you as you provide valuable feedback.

    • Reminder:

    For optimal performance, make sure you have the latest versions of SHOPsears and iOS on your device. To view this information, select About SHOPsears from the menu.

    Latest SHOPsears version: IPA 1.7
    (iPad and handheld will always have the same IPA version)
    Latest iOS version iPads and iHeld 5: 9.3.5
    Latest iOS version iHeld 4: 6.1.6

    If your device isn't running the latest version, download it immediately, or contact the SHOPsears Help Desk or Pebble Support (see below).

    SHOPsears Help Desk: 1-800-998-1500 (press 6 for SHOPsears support)

    Pebble Support: Use the Report an Issue button to report issues and concerns.

    Hoffman support team will be actively monitoring Pebble and responding as needed

    Crisis management issues will be communicated through the Retail Services ALERTS process.

    Be sure to follow the SHOPsears group on Pebble for real-time notifications of issues and fixes.
